  "doc_id": "17334",
  "text": "The current study aimed to compare the QoL of undergraduate medical students with a host of social parameters and personal habits. The higher scores for male students compared to females are concurrent with the findings of a study on medical students in Brazil [CITATION_1] and Iran, [CITATION_2] and also, of a study on university students in Serbia, [CITATION_3] all of which reported higher QoL for males. This can probably be partly explained by a traditional patriarchal society in India that confers less freedom to females than males in general and also, because of a dearth of safety for Indian women in the social scenario.",
